data.description: HUGE OPPORTUNITY! The sellers’ existing 3% loan interest rate including the added benefit of no PMI payment required which is assumable for qualified veterans and non-veterans and could save you tons money on your mortgage.    Welcome to serenity and gorgeous long-distance views in this custom built, single-level home with direct access to BLM land for miles. Ride your horse or ATV right off the property to explore the captivating landscape. Only 20 minutes from highway 395 and 30 minutes from UNR. This unique home's 16 ft. cathedral ceilings and extremely open floor plan is perfect for entertaining. With large windows throughout, natural light fills the home. The great room includes kitchen, dining room and living room with direct access to a large, covered patio with endless views. The kitchen features picture windows, stainless steel appliances, a five-burner gas stove, built in microwave and pantry.  In its own wing, the large master bedroom and bathroom with double sinks and jetted tub create a sanctuary for relaxing. A double-sided fireplace in the master bedroom and living room adds ambiance and warmth. All carpet is 100% wool. In addition to three bedrooms, the family room is a great space for media, crafting, or playroom or could be converted to a 4th bedroom. The three-car garage is 30'x30' with 10 ft. ceilings and a roughed-in addition above that could be a 4th bedroom, man cave, or office. The property is fully fenced and gated and features a recently built 11kw, owned solar system with high efficiency Solar World panels, integrated emergency power supply, and EV charging. This house will save you thousands on utility costs! The all-electric appliances, offset by the solar system, as well as the pellet stove and fireplace keep propane and electric costs extremely low. Enjoy quiet privacy at the end of a cul-de-sac with no HOA or CC&Rs and a location that adjoins expansive BLM with roaming wildlife.
